  "metadata": {
    "kin": "Human",
    "profession": "Mage",
    "age": "28 (Adult)",
    "weakness": "Slothful — Viktor always takes the laziest path and puts off anything that doesn't interest him",
    "appearance": "Viktor Vale is a tall, lean man in a battered coat, dark hair perpetually tousled, and tired eyes that always look like he's sizing up a situation—part curiosity, part caution. His posture is relaxed, often leaning on invisible walls of thought, and he rarely stands when he can conjure a seat. Around his neck, on a worn leather cord, hangs a smooth, naturally holed river stone—his hag stone—an unassuming token he fingers when lost in thought.",
    "notes": "A reluctant mentalist who prefers conjuring a chair over standing and will always find the laziest path to solving a problem — but when something buried and dangerous stirs, even sloth gives way to stubborn duty."
  },
